Name: YKL190W
genelen: CalciNeurin subunit B
function: Non-essential gene; null mutant accumulates increased amounts of calcium but shows increased sensitivity to higher concentrations of lithium and calcium; in systematic studies mutants show inositol auxotrophy, increased sensitivity to a variety of chemicals, including DTT, tunicamycin, caffeine, cycloheximide, increased resistance to MMS and mycophenolic acid; null mutant is also sensitive to osmotic and oxidative stress and shows reduced competitive fitness

Name: YDL029W
genelen: Actin-Related Protein
function: Essential/non-essential gene; null mutant has been reported to be either viable and slow growing or inviable in S288C; conditional mutant arrests non-uniformly and loses viability; conditional mutant displays abnormal actin cytoskeleton morphology, abnormal bud morphology, a random budding pattern in both haploids and diploids, abnormal chitin deposition, defective endocytosis and sensitivity to hyperosmotic stress; conditional mutant displays decreased mitochondrial movement velocity, loss of directed movement, and abnormal mitochondrial morphology; homozygous conditional diploid has a defect in spore wall formation and a severe sporulation defect; hypomorphic DAmP allele has reduced telomere length

Name: YLL050C
genelen: COFilin
function: Essential gene; conditional (ts) mutations lead to accumulation of actin filament aggregates after shift to restrictive temperature, accompanied by defects in protein secretion, endocytosis, abnormal mitochondrial morphology, and increased sensitivity to benomyl, myriocin, MMS; overexpression slows down vegetative growth due to a delay in G2 or M phase of the cell cycle
intronlen: Actin filament-binding protein that localizes to actin cortical patches; involved in  the organization, depolymerization and severing of actin filaments; also involved in endocytosis and transport of proteins from the Golgi to the plasma membrane

Name: YLR078C
genelen: Bet One Suppressor
function: Essential gene; repressible mutant accumulates 40-60 nm secretory vesicles, and an extensive network of endoplasmic reticulum; repressible mutant accumulates a precursor form of carboxypeptidase Y and pro-alpha factor, indicative of a failure in transport of proteins to the Golgi apparatus; reduction of function mutant has decreased competitive fitness in minimal medium and displays increased sensitivity to MMS and hydroxyurea; heterozygous null mutant is haploproficient; overexpression results in a decreased growth rate

function: Essential gene; repressible mutant accumulates 40-60 nm secretory vesicles, and an extensive network of endoplasmic reticulum; repressible mutant accumulates a precursor form of carboxypeptidase Y and pro-alpha factor, indicative of a failure in transport of proteins to the Golgi apparatus; reduction of function mutant has decreased competitive fitness in minimal medium and displays increased sensitivity to MMS and hydroxyurea; heterozygous null mutant is haploproficient; overexpression results in a decreased growth rate

Name: YOR122C
genelen: ProFilin of Yeast
function: Essential gene in S288C, non-essential in Sigma1278b and other strain backgrounds; null mutant in a non-essential background has a growth defect, is temperature sensitive, is larger and rounder than wt, with a decreased unipolar budding pattern, altered actin cytoskeleton morphology, delocalized chitin deposition, and is often multinucleate; null mutant has a reduced mating efficiency when cells are mating type alpha; conditional mutant displays increased chromosomal instability; heterozygous diploid null mutant has reduced starvation resistance; overexpression results in a reduced growth rate

Name: Peripheral plasma membrane protein capable of binding actin monomers, PIP2, and proline-rich regions of proteins; involved in sequestering of actin monomers and positive regulation of formin-nucleated actin cable assembly; also localizes to cytosol
genelen: SC_Transcript_00000114

function: Essential gene in S288C, non-essential in Sigma1278b and other strain backgrounds; null mutant in a non-essential background has a growth defect, is temperature sensitive, is larger and rounder than wt, with a decreased unipolar budding pattern, altered actin cytoskeleton morphology, delocalized chitin deposition, and is often multinucleate; null mutant has a reduced mating efficiency when cells are mating type alpha; conditional mutant displays increased chromosomal instability; heterozygous diploid null mutant has reduced starvation resistance; overexpression results in a reduced growth rate

Name: Peripheral plasma membrane protein capable of binding actin monomers, PIP2, and proline-rich regions of proteins; involved in sequestering of actin monomers and positive regulation of formin-nucleated actin cable assembly; also localizes to cytosol
